race.comment: SWEETHEARTED (10) closed off strongly last start beaten a long neck, over 1000m at Pakenham. Tumbles in weight and the extra metres suit. Will drift back but wind up late. BIG SWINGER (1) was well in the market finding a place at Stakes level and then ran his best number, beaten 1.3L over 1200m at Pakenham this grade. He will also present cherry-ripe and prove tough to beat. NAVAL ACADEMY (4) will lead or stalk and assess his chances on his neck defeat at Cranbourne two-back. Has a handy gate and a 2kg claim and can make the finish. MOBY DICK (6) resumes for a top metro barn with the in-form Brown a key jockey engagement. He's won 2/3 fresh and has been fitted with three jumpouts. Tipping that we'll see more from him this preparation. CARBONADOS (2) is third up and has been switched back from Sydney by the Hayes stable. Has a low barrier and a 3kg claim and keep onside.
